      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, if you're saying the border security argument is \"ethically weak\" and just \"bureaucratic,\" then aren't you basically saying that one side is just wrong and the other is right? for a debate coach, shouldn't you be able to see that the side focusing on national stability and the rule of law is also trying to protect people (like their own citizens)? or is that just an excuse people use to ignore human rights?",
